dismissalText.commentary: Alex Cusack not out 36 (56b 1x4 1x6 81m) SR: 64.28
Kenny Carroll hit wicket b Steyn 21 (24b 1x4 0x6 38m) SR: 87.5

dismissalComment.html: would you believe it, he's hit his wickets! Carroll went right back in his crease to defend a short of a length ball from Steyn, as his right leg came down, his foot slipped and caused him to fall over and hit his stumps with his back leg, I don't think his spikes were doing their job, an unfortunate way to go

edged and gone, and Philander gets his first ODI wicket on his 22nd birthday! The ball sat up from a short length and surprised Porterfield, who hopped up and fended, only to edge into Boucher's leaping gloves behind the stumps
Philander is having an excellent debut, Niall O' Brien plays all around one that swung back into him from outside off and hits off and middle stump, Ireland are really struggling now

headshotImage.caption: Kyle McCallan player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Kyle McCallan player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalComment.html: Philander has his third! He banged it in short, McCallan went down on one knee and tried to scoop it over Boucher, he ended up getting a faint nick and Boucher moved quickly to his left to take the catch
they didn't stay on this time, Whelan tries to slog across the line, he misses, Philander hits and collects his fourth wicket on debut, a fine effort from him

dismissalText.commentary: Roger Whelan b Philander 0 (7b 0x4 0x6 6m) SR: 0

commentTextItems.html: they didn't stay on this time, Whelan tries to slog across the line, he misses, Philander hits and collects his fourth wicket on debut, a fine effort from him

commentPostTextItems.html: Ireland have been dismissed for 131 which means South Africa win this game by 42 runs. Vernon Philander was the pick of the bowlers with 4 for 12 on debut. Those figures are the second best by a South African bowler on debut and seventh best of all time.

Another debutant who had an impressive debut was Alex Cusack. He had just one List A match under his belt before this game and he emerged with figures of 3 for 15 and 36 not out. That effort has won him the Man-of-the-Match award. Not a bad debut at all.

That's it from us at Cricinfo today. Thank you for waiting with us through the rain. Do join us for the first day of the Sri Lanka-Bangladesh Test that begins tomorrow in Colombo and for the first ODI between India and South Africa on Tuesday. This is George Binoy signing off. Good night all.

commentTextItems.html: how did that miss, that was unbelieveable close to off stump, it might have even clipped the edge of off stump but the bails stayed on, curiouser and curiouser
pushed into the gap at cover for a single
on the fullr side from Philander, Cusack thumps it but can't beat the man at cover

commentPreTextItems.html: This is the last over coming up.

commentTextItems.html: good length ball on off and middle stump, defended on the back foot towards cover point
and Whelan survives as the last ball whizzes past off stump
squeezed out to second slip on the bounce
Whelan makes contact with a crude flat-batted swat to mid on
Steyn bowls it shorter and gets it up to Whelan's gloves, he defends it down on the off side and looks rather uncomfortable out there
full and fast, aimed at the base off middle and leg stump, Whelan moves forward and defends back to the bowler

commentPreTextItems.html: Whelan is the last man in.

commentTextItems.html: flicked off the pads to deep square leg

dismissalText.commentary: Kyle McCallan c †Boucher b Philander 10 (12b 0x4 0x6 25m) SR: 83.33

commentTextItems.html: Philander has his third! He banged it in short, McCallan went down on one knee and tried to scoop it over Boucher, he ended up getting a faint nick and Boucher moved quickly to his left to take the catch
Cusack backs away, makes room and lofts over cover
short ball outside the off stump, Cusack tries to get under it and cut it down to third man but fails to make contact
defended to point on the front foot

commentPreTextItems.html: Vernon Philander returns for a second spell. Three overs remain.

commentTextItems.html: McCallan leans forward and drives him superbly through point, the ball's timed really well but Duminy is equally superb at saving the boundary with a well-timed dive
played off the back foot towards point

dismissalText.commentary: Dom Joyce c †Boucher b Kallis 11 (19b 2x4 0x6 27m) SR: 57.89

dismissalComment.html: pitches on a good length outside off stump and holds it's line, Joyce tries to drive off the back foot and ends up playing away from his body, the ball hits the outside edge and Boucher takes a low catch, Ireland have lost their fifth wicket

stories.title: Primed South Africa can't take the Irish lightly
stories.subTitle: Ireland v South Africa, One-off ODI, Belfast
stories.summary:
On paper the match against a
depleted Ireland side is the ideal way to ease into their short
one-day tour of the Emerald Isle, but they would be well advised not
take anything for granted
